{"paragraphs":[{"cues":[{"time":2000,"text":"To understand the business of mythology"},{"time":5000,"text":"and what a Chief Belief Officer is supposed to do,"},{"time":9000,"text":"you have to hear a story"},{"time":11000,"text":"of Ganesha,"},{"time":13000,"text":"the elephant-headed god"},{"time":15000,"text":"who is the scribe of storytellers,"},{"time":18000,"text":"and his brother,"},{"time":19000,"text":"the athletic warlord of the gods,"},{"time":21000,"text":"Kartikeya."},{"time":23000,"text":"The two brothers one day decided to go on a race,"},{"time":26000,"text":"three times around the world."},{"time":29000,"text":"Kartikeya leapt on his peacock"},{"time":32000,"text":"and flew around the continents"},{"time":35000,"text":"and the mountains and the oceans."},{"time":40000,"text":"He went around once,"},{"time":42000,"text":"he went around twice,"},{"time":44000,"text":"he went around thrice."},{"time":47000,"text":"But his brother, Ganesha,"},{"time":50000,"text":"simply walked around his parents"},{"time":53000,"text":"once, twice, thrice,"},{"time":55000,"text":"and said, \"I won.\""},{"time":58000,"text":"\"How come?\" said Kartikeya."},{"time":60000,"text":"And Ganesha said,"},{"time":61000,"text":"\"You went around 'the world.'"},{"time":64000,"text":"I went around 'my world.'\""},{"time":67000,"text":"What matters more?"}]},{"cues":[{"time":70000,"text":"If you understand the difference between 'the world' and 'my world,'"},{"time":73000,"text":"you understand the difference between logos and mythos."},{"time":77000,"text":"'The world' is objective,"},{"time":79000,"text":"logical, universal, factual,"},{"time":82000,"text":"scientific."},{"time":84000,"text":"'My world' is subjective."},{"time":87000,"text":"It's emotional. It's personal."},{"time":90000,"text":"It's perceptions, thoughts, feelings, dreams."},{"time":93000,"text":"It is the belief system that we carry."},{"time":96000,"text":"It's the myth that we live in."}]},{"cues":[{"time":99000,"text":"'The world' tells us how the world functions,"},{"time":102000,"text":"how the sun rises,"},{"time":105000,"text":"how we are born."},{"time":108000,"text":"'My world' tells us why the sun rises,"},{"time":111000,"text":"why we were born."},{"time":115000,"text":"Every culture is trying to understand itself:"},{"time":119000,"text":"\"Why do we exist?\""},{"time":121000,"text":"And every culture comes up with its own understanding of life,"},{"time":124000,"text":"its own customized version of mythology."}]},{"cues":[{"time":129000,"text":"Culture is a reaction to nature,"},{"time":132000,"text":"and this understanding of our ancestors"},{"time":134000,"text":"is transmitted generation from generation"},{"time":137000,"text":"in the form of stories, symbols and rituals,"},{"time":140000,"text":"which are always indifferent to rationality."},{"time":146000,"text":"And so, when you study it, you realize"},{"time":148000,"text":"that different people of the world"},{"time":150000,"text":"have a different understanding of the world."},{"time":153000,"text":"Different people see things differently --"},{"time":155000,"text":"different viewpoints."}]},{"cues":[{"time":157000,"text":"There is my world and there is your world,"},{"time":159000,"text":"and my world is always better than your world,"},{"time":162000,"text":"because my world, you see, is rational"},{"time":165000,"text":"and yours is superstition."},{"time":167000,"text":"Yours is faith."},{"time":169000,"text":"Yours is illogical."},{"time":172000,"text":"This is the root of the clash of civilizations."},{"time":175000,"text":"It took place, once, in 326 B.C."},{"time":179000,"text":"on the banks of a river called the Indus,"},{"time":182000,"text":"now in Pakistan."},{"time":184000,"text":"This river lends itself to India's name."},{"time":187000,"text":"India. Indus."}]},{"cues":[{"time":192000,"text":"Alexander, a young Macedonian,"},{"time":195000,"text":"met there what he called a \"gymnosophist,\""},{"time":199000,"text":"which means \"the naked, wise man.\""},{"time":202000,"text":"We don't know who he was."},{"time":204000,"text":"Perhaps he was a Jain monk,"},{"time":206000,"text":"like Bahubali over here,"},{"time":208000,"text":"the Gomateshwara Bahubali"},{"time":209000,"text":"whose image is not far from Mysore."},{"time":211000,"text":"Or perhaps he was just a yogi"},{"time":213000,"text":"who was sitting on a rock, staring at the sky"},{"time":215000,"text":"and the sun and the moon."}]},{"cues":[{"time":217000,"text":"Alexander asked, \"What are you doing?\""},{"time":220000,"text":"and the gymnosophist answered,"},{"time":222000,"text":"\"I'm experiencing nothingness.\""},{"time":225000,"text":"Then the gymnosophist asked,"},{"time":228000,"text":"\"What are you doing?\""},{"time":230000,"text":"and Alexander said, \"I am conquering the world.\""},{"time":233000,"text":"And they both laughed."},{"time":236000,"text":"Each one thought that the other was a fool."},{"time":240000,"text":"The gymnosophist said, \"Why is he conquering the world?"},{"time":244000,"text":"It's pointless.\""},{"time":247000,"text":"And Alexander thought,"},{"time":249000,"text":"\"Why is he sitting around, doing nothing?"},{"time":251000,"text":"What a waste of a life.\""}]},{"cues":[{"time":253000,"text":"To understand this difference in viewpoints,"},{"time":257000,"text":"we have to understand"},{"time":260000,"text":"the subjective truth of Alexander --"},{"time":263000,"text":"his myth, and the mythology that constructed it."},{"time":268000,"text":"Alexander's mother, his parents, his teacher Aristotle"},{"time":271000,"text":"told him the story of Homer's \"Iliad.\""},{"time":274000,"text":"They told him of a great hero called Achilles,"},{"time":277000,"text":"who, when he participated in battle, victory was assured,"},{"time":280000,"text":"but when he withdrew from the battle,"},{"time":283000,"text":"defeat was inevitable."},{"time":286000,"text":"\"Achilles was a man who could shape history,"},{"time":289000,"text":"a man of destiny,"},{"time":292000,"text":"and this is what you should be, Alexander.\""},{"time":295000,"text":"That's what he heard."}]},{"cues":[{"time":297000,"text":"\"What should you not be?"},{"time":300000,"text":"You should not be Sisyphus,"},{"time":303000,"text":"who rolls a rock up a mountain all day"},{"time":305000,"text":"only to find the boulder rolled down at night."},{"time":310000,"text":"Don't live a life which is monotonous,"},{"time":313000,"text":"mediocre, meaningless."},{"time":315000,"text":"Be spectacular! --"},{"time":318000,"text":"like the Greek heroes,"},{"time":320000,"text":"like Jason, who went across the sea"},{"time":322000,"text":"with the Argonauts and fetched the Golden Fleece."},{"time":326000,"text":"Be spectacular like Theseus,"},{"time":329000,"text":"who entered the labyrinth and killed the bull-headed Minotaur."},{"time":335000,"text":"When you play in a race, win! --"},{"time":339000,"text":"because when you win, the exhilaration of victory"},{"time":342000,"text":"is the closest you will come to the ambrosia of the gods.\""}]},{"cues":[{"time":347000,"text":"Because, you see, the Greeks believed"},{"time":350000,"text":"you live only once,"},{"time":352000,"text":"and when you die, you have to cross the River Styx."},{"time":356000,"text":"And if you have lived an extraordinary life,"},{"time":359000,"text":"you will be welcomed to Elysium,"},{"time":362000,"text":"or what the French call \"Champs-Élysées\" --"},{"time":366000,"text":"(Laughter) --"},{"time":367000,"text":"the heaven of the heroes."}]},{"cues":[{"time":373000,"text":"But these are not the stories that the gymnosophist heard."},{"time":377000,"text":"He heard a very different story."},{"time":380000,"text":"He heard of a man called Bharat,"},{"time":383000,"text":"after whom India is called Bhārata."},{"time":386000,"text":"Bharat also conquered the world."},{"time":389000,"text":"And then he went to the top-most peak"},{"time":392000,"text":"of the greatest mountain of the center of the world"},{"time":395000,"text":"called Meru."},{"time":396000,"text":"And he wanted to hoist his flag to say,"},{"time":399000,"text":"\"I was here first.\""},{"time":402000,"text":"But when he reached the mountain peak,"},{"time":404000,"text":"he found the peak covered with countless flags"},{"time":409000,"text":"of world-conquerors before him,"},{"time":412000,"text":"each one claiming \"'I was here first' ..."},{"time":416000,"text":"that's what I thought until I came here.\""},{"time":420000,"text":"And suddenly, in this canvas of infinity,"},{"time":423000,"text":"Bharat felt insignificant."},{"time":427000,"text":"This was the mythology of the gymnosophist."}]},{"cues":[{"time":431000,"text":"You see, he had heroes, like Ram -- Raghupati Ram"},{"time":436000,"text":"and Krishna, Govinda Hari."},{"time":438000,"text":"But they were not two characters on two different adventures."},{"time":442000,"text":"They were two lifetimes of the same hero."},{"time":446000,"text":"When the Ramayana ends the Mahabharata begins."},{"time":450000,"text":"When Ram dies, Krishna is born."},{"time":452000,"text":"When Krishna dies, eventually he will be back as Ram."}]},{"cues":[{"time":455000,"text":"You see, the Indians also had a river"},{"time":458000,"text":"that separates the land of the living from the land of the dead."},{"time":461000,"text":"But you don't cross it once."},{"time":463000,"text":"You go to and fro endlessly."},{"time":466000,"text":"It was called the Vaitarani."},{"time":469000,"text":"You go again and again and again."},{"time":472000,"text":"Because, you see,"},{"time":473000,"text":"nothing lasts forever in India, not even death."},{"time":476000,"text":"And so, you have these grand rituals"},{"time":479000,"text":"where great images of mother goddesses are built"},{"time":482000,"text":"and worshiped for 10 days ..."},{"time":484000,"text":"And what do you do at the end of 10 days?"},{"time":486000,"text":"You dunk it in the river."},{"time":489000,"text":"Because it has to end."},{"time":491000,"text":"And next year, she will come back."},{"time":494000,"text":"What goes around always comes around,"},{"time":496000,"text":"and this rule applies not just to man,"},{"time":499000,"text":"but also the gods."},{"time":501000,"text":"You see, the gods"},{"time":504000,"text":"have to come back again and again and again"},{"time":506000,"text":"as Ram, as Krishna."},{"time":508000,"text":"Not only do they live infinite lives,"},{"time":511000,"text":"but the same life is lived infinite times"},{"time":514000,"text":"till you get to the point of it all."},{"time":519000,"text":"\"Groundhog Day.\""},{"time":521000,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":526000,"text":"Two different mythologies."},{"time":529000,"text":"Which is right?"},{"time":531000,"text":"Two different mythologies, two different ways of looking at the world."},{"time":534000,"text":"One linear, one cyclical."},{"time":536000,"text":"One believes this is the one and only life."},{"time":538000,"text":"The other believes this is one of many lives."},{"time":543000,"text":"And so, the denominator of Alexander's life was one."},{"time":547000,"text":"So, the value of his life was the sum total"},{"time":550000,"text":"of his achievements."},{"time":552000,"text":"The denominator of the gymnosophist's life was infinity."},{"time":556000,"text":"So, no matter what he did,"},{"time":559000,"text":"it was always zero."},{"time":561000,"text":"And I believe it is this mythological paradigm"},{"time":564000,"text":"that inspired Indian mathematicians"},{"time":567000,"text":"to discover the number zero."},{"time":569000,"text":"Who knows?"}]},{"cues":[{"time":571000,"text":"And that brings us to the mythology of business."},{"time":574000,"text":"If Alexander's belief influenced his behavior,"},{"time":577000,"text":"if the gymnosophist's belief influences his behavior,"},{"time":581000,"text":"then it was bound to influence the business they were in."},{"time":586000,"text":"You see, what is business"},{"time":588000,"text":"but the result of how the market behaves"},{"time":590000,"text":"and how the organization behaves?"},{"time":593000,"text":"And if you look at cultures around the world,"},{"time":596000,"text":"all you have to do is understand the mythology"},{"time":598000,"text":"and you will see how they behave and how they do business."}]},{"cues":[{"time":601000,"text":"Take a look."},{"time":605000,"text":"If you live only once, in one-life cultures around the world,"},{"time":608000,"text":"you will see an obsession with binary logic,"},{"time":610000,"text":"absolute truth, standardization,"},{"time":613000,"text":"absoluteness, linear patterns in design."},{"time":616000,"text":"But if you look at cultures which have cyclical"},{"time":619000,"text":"and based on infinite lives, you will see a comfort with fuzzy logic,"},{"time":624000,"text":"with opinion,"},{"time":626000,"text":"with contextual thinking,"},{"time":628000,"text":"with everything is relative, sort of --"},{"time":631000,"text":"(Laughter)"},{"time":632000,"text":"mostly."},{"time":634000,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":635000,"text":"You look at art. Look at the ballerina,"},{"time":638000,"text":"how linear she is in her performance."},{"time":640000,"text":"And then look at the Indian classical dancer,"},{"time":642000,"text":"the Kuchipudi dancer, the Bharatanatyam dancer,"},{"time":644000,"text":"curvaceous."},{"time":646000,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":649000,"text":"And then look at business."},{"time":651000,"text":"Standard business model:"},{"time":653000,"text":"vision, mission, values, processes."},{"time":657000,"text":"Sounds very much like the journey through"},{"time":659000,"text":"the wilderness to the promised land,"},{"time":661000,"text":"with the commandments held by the leader."},{"time":663000,"text":"And if you comply, you will go to heaven."}]},{"cues":[{"time":668000,"text":"But in India there is no \"the\" promised land."},{"time":670000,"text":"There are many promised lands,"},{"time":673000,"text":"depending on your station in society,"},{"time":676000,"text":"depending on your stage of life."},{"time":678000,"text":"You see, businesses are not run as institutions,"},{"time":682000,"text":"by the idiosyncrasies of individuals."},{"time":685000,"text":"It's always about taste."},{"time":688000,"text":"It's always about my taste."}]},{"cues":[{"time":692000,"text":"You see, Indian music, for example,"},{"time":694000,"text":"does not have the concept of harmony."},{"time":696000,"text":"There is no orchestra conductor."},{"time":700000,"text":"There is one performer standing there, and everybody follows."},{"time":703000,"text":"And you can never replicate that performance twice."},{"time":707000,"text":"It is not about documentation and contract."},{"time":709000,"text":"It's about conversation and faith."},{"time":713000,"text":"It's not about compliance. It's about setting,"},{"time":717000,"text":"getting the job done, by bending or breaking the rules --"},{"time":721000,"text":"just look at your Indian people around here,"},{"time":723000,"text":"you'll see them smile; they know what it is."},{"time":725000,"text":"(Laughter)"},{"time":726000,"text":"And then look at people who have done business in India,"},{"time":728000,"text":"you'll see the exasperation on their faces."},{"time":730000,"text":"(Laughter)"},{"time":731000,"text":"(Applause)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":735000,"text":"You see, this is what India is today. The ground reality"},{"time":737000,"text":"is based on a cyclical world view."},{"time":739000,"text":"So, it's rapidly changing, highly diverse,"},{"time":742000,"text":"chaotic, ambiguous, unpredictable."},{"time":745000,"text":"And people are okay with it."},{"time":748000,"text":"And then globalization is taking place."},{"time":750000,"text":"The demands of modern institutional thinking is coming in."},{"time":754000,"text":"Which is rooted in one-life culture."},{"time":758000,"text":"And a clash is going to take place,"},{"time":760000,"text":"like on the banks of the Indus."},{"time":763000,"text":"It is bound to happen."}]},{"cues":[{"time":766000,"text":"I have personally experienced it. I'm trained as a medical doctor."},{"time":769000,"text":"I did not want to study surgery. Don't ask me why."},{"time":772000,"text":"I love mythology too much."},{"time":774000,"text":"I wanted to learn mythology. But there is nowhere you can study."},{"time":776000,"text":"So, I had to teach it to myself."},{"time":778000,"text":"And mythology does not pay, well, until now."},{"time":781000,"text":"(Laughter)"},{"time":785000,"text":"So, I had to take up a job. And I worked in the pharma industry."},{"time":788000,"text":"And I worked in the healthcare industry."},{"time":790000,"text":"And I worked as a marketing guy, and a sales guy,"},{"time":792000,"text":"and a knowledge guy, and a content guy, and a training guy."},{"time":795000,"text":"I even was a business consultant, doing strategies and tactics."},{"time":798000,"text":"And I would see the exasperation"},{"time":800000,"text":"between my American and European colleagues,"},{"time":803000,"text":"when they were dealing with India."}]},{"cues":[{"time":805000,"text":"Example: Please tell us the process"},{"time":808000,"text":"to invoice hospitals."},{"time":811000,"text":"Step A. Step B. Step C. Mostly."},{"time":815000,"text":"(Laughter)"},{"time":817000,"text":"How do you parameterize \"mostly\"?"},{"time":819000,"text":"How do you put it in a nice little software? You can't."}]},{"cues":[{"time":823000,"text":"I would give my viewpoints to people."},{"time":825000,"text":"But nobody was interested in listening to it,"},{"time":827000,"text":"you see, until I met Kishore Biyani of the Future group."},{"time":831000,"text":"You see, he has established the largest retail chain, called Big Bazaar."},{"time":836000,"text":"And there are more than 200 formats,"},{"time":838000,"text":"across 50 cities and towns of India."},{"time":840000,"text":"And he was dealing with diverse and dynamic markets."},{"time":844000,"text":"And he knew very intuitively,"},{"time":846000,"text":"that best practices,"},{"time":848000,"text":"developed in Japan and China and Europe and America"},{"time":851000,"text":"will not work in India."},{"time":854000,"text":"He knew that institutional thinking doesn't work in India. Individual thinking does."},{"time":858000,"text":"He had an intuitive understanding of the mythic structure of India."}]},{"cues":[{"time":862000,"text":"So, he had asked me to be the Chief Belief Officer, and said,"},{"time":864000,"text":"\"All I want to do is align belief.\""},{"time":867000,"text":"Sounds so simple."},{"time":869000,"text":"But belief is not measurable."},{"time":871000,"text":"You can't measure it. You can't manage it."},{"time":873000,"text":"So, how do you construct belief?"},{"time":875000,"text":"How do you enhance the sensitivity of people to Indian-ness."},{"time":879000,"text":"Even if you are Indian, it is not very explicit, it is not very obvious."}]},{"cues":[{"time":883000,"text":"So, I tried to work on the standard model of culture,"},{"time":887000,"text":"which is, develop stories, symbols and rituals."},{"time":889000,"text":"And I will share one of the rituals with you."},{"time":892000,"text":"You see it is based on the Hindu ritual of Darshan."},{"time":895000,"text":"Hindus don't have the concept of commandments."},{"time":897000,"text":"So, there is nothing right or wrong in what you do in life."},{"time":899000,"text":"So, you're not really sure how you stand in front of God."},{"time":902000,"text":"So, when you go to the temple, all you seek is an audience with God."},{"time":905000,"text":"You want to see God."},{"time":907000,"text":"And you want God to see you, and hence the gods have very large eyes,"},{"time":911000,"text":"large unblinking eyes,"},{"time":913000,"text":"sometimes made of silver,"},{"time":916000,"text":"so they look at you."},{"time":918000,"text":"Because you don't know whether you're right or wrong, and so all you seek"},{"time":920000,"text":"is divine empathy."},{"time":924000,"text":"\"Just know where I came from, why I did the Jugaad.\""},{"time":927000,"text":"(Laughter)"},{"time":928000,"text":"\"Why did I do the setting,"},{"time":930000,"text":"why I don't care for the processes. Just understand me, please.\""}]},{"cues":[{"time":935000,"text":"And based on this, we created a ritual for leaders."},{"time":938000,"text":"After a leader completes his training and is about to take over the store,"},{"time":942000,"text":"we blindfold him, we surround him with the stakeholders,"},{"time":946000,"text":"the customer, his family, his team, his boss."},{"time":950000,"text":"You read out his KRA, his KPI, you give him the keys,"},{"time":953000,"text":"and then you remove the blindfold."},{"time":955000,"text":"And invariably, you see a tear,"},{"time":958000,"text":"because the penny has dropped."},{"time":960000,"text":"He realizes that to succeed,"},{"time":964000,"text":"he does not have to be a \"professional,\""},{"time":967000,"text":"he does not have to cut out his emotions,"},{"time":970000,"text":"he has to include all these people"},{"time":973000,"text":"in his world to succeed, to make them happy,"},{"time":977000,"text":"to make the boss happy, to make everyone happy."},{"time":979000,"text":"The customer is happy, because the customer is God."}]},{"cues":[{"time":982000,"text":"That sensitivity is what we need. Once this belief enters,"},{"time":985000,"text":"behavior will happen, business will happen."},{"time":988000,"text":"And it has."},{"time":991000,"text":"So, then we come back to Alexander"},{"time":994000,"text":"and to the gymnosophist."},{"time":996000,"text":"And everybody asks me, \"Which is the better way, this way or that way?\""},{"time":1000000,"text":"And it's a very dangerous question,"},{"time":1002000,"text":"because it leads you to the path of fundamentalism and violence."},{"time":1006000,"text":"So, I will not answer the question."},{"time":1008000,"text":"What I will give you is an Indian answer,"},{"time":1010000,"text":"the Indian head-shake."},{"time":1012000,"text":"(Laughter)"},{"time":1014000,"text":"(Applause)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":1018000,"text":"Depending on the context,"},{"time":1020000,"text":"depending on the outcome,"},{"time":1022000,"text":"choose your paradigm."},{"time":1025000,"text":"You see, because both the paradigms are human constructions."},{"time":1028000,"text":"They are cultural creations,"},{"time":1031000,"text":"not natural phenomena."},{"time":1034000,"text":"And so the next time you meet someone, a stranger,"},{"time":1037000,"text":"one request:"},{"time":1039000,"text":"Understand that you live in the subjective truth,"},{"time":1042000,"text":"and so does he."},{"time":1044000,"text":"Understand it."},{"time":1046000,"text":"And when you understand it you will discover something spectacular."},{"time":1051000,"text":"You will discover that within infinite myths"},{"time":1053000,"text":"lies the eternal truth."},{"time":1055000,"text":"Who sees it all?"},{"time":1057000,"text":"Varuna has but a thousand eyes."},{"time":1059000,"text":"Indra, a hundred."},{"time":1062000,"text":"You and I, only two."},{"time":1064000,"text":"Thank you. Namaste."},{"time":1067000,"text":"(Applause)"}]}]}